2012-10-04  Reuben Thomas <rrt@sc3d.org>

	* .gitignore, Makefile, NEWS, mkrockspecs.lua, rockspecs.lua,
	src/common.mak, src/defaults.mak, src/gnu/Makefile,
	src/oniguruma/Makefile, src/pcre/Makefile, src/posix/Makefile,
	src/tre/Makefile, test/onig_sets.lua, test/oniguruma_sets.lua,
	test/runtest.lua, windows/mingw/Makefile, windows/mingw/_mingw.mak,
	windows/mingw/docs.mak, windows/mingw/rex_gnu.mak,
	windows/mingw/rex_onig.mak, windows/mingw/rex_pcre.mak,
	windows/mingw/rex_spencer.mak, windows/mingw/rex_tre.mak: Replace
	build systems with LuaRocks.  A single Makefile remains to take care of tests, distribution,
	release and documentation.  As a result, rockspecs are automatically generated for all lrexlib
	flavours (previously, only POSIX and PCRE were available).

2012-10-04  Reuben Thomas <rrt@sc3d.org>

	* src/defaults.mak: defaults.mak: add -fPIC and remove -g from
	default gcc flags

